{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "She did a lot of those under the worst circumstances, in total secret, risking her life every time she did it, but trying to save a life every time she would do it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "Working in the hospital, our physical comforts, of course, were a little better.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "But we paid dearly in other ways.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Dr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "Mengele came every single day, and at least once or twice a week, he would order us how many people he wants for the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "He would do the selection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "But we who worked there, we had to guide those people out to the waiting trucks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And the longer we worked there, the more of us and the more of them knew where they're going and what is happening.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "Also sometimes we had dead bodies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "Not too often, but we did have some.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "We would then have to put those dead bodies on the trucks, more often than not with the people who are alive, to be taken to the same place.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "Of course, I remember when first I had to do it, I came back, and I couldn't eat my little piece of bread for dinner.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "But I suppose your spirit to survive, even subconsciously, is stronger than anything else.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "After awhile, you just wash your hand as well as you can, and you eat your bread, because hunger is probably the strongest emotion, and strongest feeling that you have.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "And even if you don't know that you want to-- but basically, you do want to survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "I almost had a chance to save a life once, but it didn't work out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "One day the hospital was basically three barracks, and they were connected by one hallway, the three barracks.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
